annotation.TEXT: This is so sweet! I'd better make sure I don't make any stupid mistakes now!
Oh, well. Let's shoot some blocky fish.
Strong enough to quickly turn Bowser into a gray version of the player character from the Atari 2600 game Adventure.
SMBS demo count: 1
Oh, and I got the six fireworks too. Good.
Oh, there's no music again. D'oh. Let me see if I can fix that again...
This level seems largely similar to the original SMB's 2-2, which I guess isn't that surprising.
Alright, so will the next character I pick be Luigi or Samus? Yes.
I'll take that Long Beam mushroom, thank you very much.
There we go, back to Vampire Killer again. It must be stuck on that tune or something. Whatever.
Yeah, of course there are flying cheepos.
Alright, now Luigi, Samus, and Random each got 2 votes, so I guess those will be what I go with for the rest of world 2. I'll pick Random now, just in case it decides on Luigi or Samus.
Ooh, gimme that star!
Oh, I can get in there if I bomb jump... or if I just morph ball while ascending, which is easier and faster!
MWAHAHA!!! All shall bow down before the almighty AWESOME SPREAD GUN!!! (Except Buzzy Beetles and Bullet Bills, who have diplomatic immunity to it.)
(This low bridge here is where midpoint actually is.)
Alright, something that's not Vampire Killer. Now, don't get me wrong. Vampire Killer is a good song, but it doesn't exactly fit a water level.
(At least, I think it was a toad, or some sort of toad-like creature.)
Now, before I finish the level, there's one pipe back here I didn't check because I was chasing a 1-up.

Oh, yeah. Someone voted for a contest to see who could clear out a bonus room full of bricks with a fully powered up character the fastest. I bet I know who'd probably be the best man for the job if such a contest were held!
Yeah, this level was mostly the same as the original's 2-3, aside from slight variances in the positions of stuff and that row of three coin ? blocks.
I can still kick stunned koopas, which is nice.
Oh, what's this? Can I enter that pipe down there?
Let's go with the NES SMB2 brand of Luigi.
D'oh! Well, so much for getting 5000 from the flag, but I'm still gonna get the 6 fireworks at least!
I think that was a glitch that was already mentioned on the Exploding Rabbit forums, where if you morph ball while ascending, Samus can pass through invisible blocks without hitting them.
Unnecessary bomb jumping FTW!
Whoa! Maybe I can fall off a platform to spice things up...
Oh, farfignewton! That sucks...
Screw you, "L"! "S" is where it's at! (And "R" is okay, too.)
So, which of these non-toad-like creatures should I use for world 3? Place your votes now!
Hello, and welcome back to B-Daman CrossFire! ...Wait, that's not right. Welcome back to SMB Crossover!
Well, I suppose that counts as a bonus area, but I doubt it'll be loaded with bricks...
And suddenly I'm underground at the ending staircase, flag, and castle. Sure, why not?
Huh, I'm surprised I got 800 from as low as I was. I expected to get only 400 there.
I wonder what, if anything, was to the right over there... I would've screen scrolled with "R", but this isn't SMW.
Yada, yada. He can shoot various ways and dies in one hit. Yada, yada.
I'm really hoping to enter a bonus room with loads of bricks for me to shred apart right now!
I guess my reward is just a bunch of additional coins. Alright, that's fine.
Wow, why did I hesitate in midair there? I have no idea.
And, yep. We've got a water level here, just like with 2-2 of the original SMB.
I wonder if this level's gonna have flying cheepos like in the original's 2-3?
I doubt I can enter any upside-down pipes, but I may as well check anyway.
Morph ball FTW!
Oh, man. Which pipe should I go through? Umm... I pick... the upper one!
Oh, nuts. Is there no music again? That seems to be a known bug involving some of Bass's skins, which will be fixed in the next version of the game, from what I've been told.
Ooh, an "R" to go with it! One more "R" and I'll be maxed out!
And so, I've rescued a toad. But, not one of SMB's Toads!
Yep, and I end up in an underground area where I'm no longer swimming. Well, that's an interesting twist, and maybe that means I'll have chances to power up in this level.
Votes for Google to change the comments back: At least 223,240.
Yeah, yeah. We all know how Samus works now.
Too bad Gemini Man is functionally no different from Bass in this game. It would've been cool if Gemini Man's shots reflected off of walls, like the Gemini Laser does in Mega Man 3.
But, for those of you not looking for a Mathematician's Answer, I'm picking Luigi next.
Alright, now it's Samus's turn, and since one of the alt. skin votes was for the Metroid II Samus, that's what I'll go with.
...And this pipe, which most certainly didn't exist in the original 2-3... Oh, and it's two-way. Interesting...

And that's as far as the pipe took me in the first place. I'm guessing it was made two-way in case the player was unable to break the brick to the right in order to escape (like if someone got here small and revealed the hidden block first, trapping the mushroom).
I'm not going to risk my life for every single one of those coins.
Ooh, a missile pickup! That was perfect timing for boss time, against Atari Bowser!
Oh, but I wasn't expecting those additional hidden blocks. Maybe they're there to keep the player from jumping on the roof (like that'll stop somebody like a hovering Sophia III...).
Yeah, yeah. I'm running out of time. Well, I've checked the pipe, so now I'm outta here!

Oh, what? I'm back to start? Did I not pass midpoint? Or, do SMB Special levels even have midpoints? (I checked this later, and this level does have a midpoint, but I just hadn't quite reached it, as it was further ahead than I expected.)

Yeah, that star was mostly wasted, but I wanted to backtrack to check every pipe for a possible underground bonus room. Unfortunately, I don't really have the time to do any further checking. If I did miss an underground bonus room in 2-1, let me know!
Well, it appears that the RNG has picked Gemini Man, which is a Bass skin.
Alright, well doing that got some music playing, although I doubt Castlevania's Vampire Killer theme really fits here, but it's better than nothing.
3-1 votes: 1
OH, YES! YES! YES! AWESOME SPREAD GUN right out the door!
And so we've got another bonus room in a castle.
I assume that candle is a fire flower. I should be able to duck-jump up to reach it... if I don't somehow enter the pipe even though I wasn't centered on it... D'oh!
To be continued...
Note: You are allowed to vote for Toad (a Mario skin) if you want. (Also, if Toad Man was one of the Mega Man or Bass skins, you'd be allowed to vote for him too.)
BARF! Wow, 100 is just... wrong. But, at least I got the six fireworks.
They probably both led to this same place, but if the lower pipe actually went somewhere else, let me know!
This is strikingly similar to the original game's 2-3 so far, but maybe there'll be another side area to spice things up.
Yes! I got the 5000 this time (even though no number appeared)! See, I can hit the top of the flagpole when I'm not incompetent!
Whoa! That was close!
Okay, there's obviously gonna be a hidden block there to allow me to enter that pipe.
I wonder exactly how much more powerful missiles are vs. my regular shots?

We got a lot more votes here than last time. The alt. skin votes included Metroid II Samus, Dr. Light (Mega Man), and Dr. Wily (Bass). Also, there was a vote for a Super Smash Bros. character, which I assumed meant Mario, Luigi, Link, or Samus. Is that right?
Oh, there's a hidden 1-up there. Wait, how come I didn't hit the hidden 1-up block when I initially jumped into that passage?
Well, it's nice to know the flower stayed there, but I wouldn't have been able to reach it even if I was able to duck jump there, due to that hidden block.
Well, anyway, the AWESOME SPREAD GUN guy won it, so let's start with him first! And, I think I'll go with his Atari skin this time!
Alright, now let's not fall off a platform to my doom this time...
